title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.1 ENABLING ENVIRONMENT

description.narrative: Output 1 (Child protection policies): National and subnational governments and stakeholders have improved knowledge, capacity, data and clear accountability to enact and implement gender responsive, inclusive and evidence-based laws, policies and budgets on child protection., which contributes to Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys are progressively empowered and protected from violence, exploitation, neglect and harmful practices by functioning, quality child protection systems and positive social norms at national and subnational level including in humanitarian settings.

title.narrative: Output 1 (Child protection policies): National and subnational governments and stakeholders have improved knowledge, capacity,data and clear accountability to enact and implement gender responsive, inclusive and evidence-based laws, policies and budgets onchild protection.

description.narrative: During the first year of the Country Programme, UNICEF’s support to the protection of children resulted in significantly advancing the development of three key national policies and strategies in line with international standards and principles. UNICEF’s support to the Government of Indonesia helped to not only improve evidence-based policy formulation but also to build the capacity of policy-makers and development planners, all of whom play critical roles in the annual programme budgetary allocation for child protection. At subnational levels, UNICEF continued to strengthen local regulations to reflect provisions for improving the quality of integrated child protection services.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/11/2021
